---
import "@/styles/global.css";
import { Navbar21 } from "@/components/sections/Navbar21";
import { Footer30 } from "@/components/sections/Footer30";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>Privacy Policy / Privacy Notice | Sewing at Aga's</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Navbar21 client:load />

    <main class="bg-white py-16 md:py-24">
      <section class="mx-auto w-full max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-black sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy / Privacy Notice</h1>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm leading-7 text-neutral-700 sm:text-base">
          <p><strong>Privacy Policy (Privacy Notice) — Sewing At Aga’s</strong></p>
          <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 13 February 2026<br /><strong>Business name:</strong> Sewing At Aga’s<br /><strong>Data controller:</strong> Sewing At Aga’s</p>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">1) Who to contact</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">If you have questions about this notice or your data, contact:</p>
            <p class="mt-2">Email: sewingataga@gmail.com</p>
            <p>Phone/WhatsApp: 07514 776088</p>
            <p>Address: 4 Victoria Rd, Poole BH12 3BB, United Kingdom</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">2) What this notice covers</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">This notice explains how we collect, use, store, and share personal information when you:</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>visit our website,</li>
              <li>contact us (phone, email, WhatsApp, contact form, social media),</li>
              <li>bring items for alterations/repairs (walk-ins),</li>
              <li>or ask about pricing and services.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2">UK privacy law is mainly the UK GDPR plus the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">3) What personal data we collect</h2>
            <p class="mt-2"><strong>A) Data you give us</strong></p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>Contact details: name, phone number, email, WhatsApp handle</li>
              <li>Message content: what you ask us, any details you include</li>
              <li>Service info: what you bring in, requested alterations, measurements you provide, fitting notes</li>
              <li>Special instructions: e.g., timing preferences, collection notes</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4"><strong>B) Data we may create during service</strong></p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>Job notes (e.g., what was done, dates, adjustments)</li>
              <li>Receipts / proof of service (if you issue them)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4"><strong>C) Website technical data (small and boring, but real)</strong></p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>basic logs such as IP address, device/browser info, and timestamps (typically via hosting/security tools)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2">We don’t intentionally collect special category data (health, religion, etc.). If you voluntarily share it in a message, we’ll treat it carefully and only use it to respond or deliver the service.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">4) Why we use your data (and our lawful bases)</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">We only use personal data when we have a legal basis under UK GDPR. Common ones for a tailor are:</p>
            <p class="mt-2"><strong>A) To respond to enquiries and provide services</strong></p>
            <p>Purpose: reply to your messages, discuss options/pricing, carry out alterations/repairs, manage collection/updates.</p>
            <p>Lawful basis: contract (or steps before a contract) and/or legitimate interests (running a small service business).</p>
            <p class="mt-4"><strong>B) To keep basic records</strong></p>
            <p>Purpose: admin, accounting, handling disputes, keeping job history for quality and continuity.</p>
            <p>Lawful basis: legal obligation (where applicable) and/or legitimate interests.</p>
            <p class="mt-4"><strong>C) Marketing (only if you choose it)</strong></p>
            <p>Purpose: updates or offers (e.g., if you explicitly ask to be kept in the loop).</p>
            <p>Lawful basis: typically consent (and you can withdraw it any time).</p>
            <p class="mt-4"><strong>D) Photos (only with permission)</strong></p>
            <p>If we ever use photos of work (e.g., garments) for portfolio/social media, we will do so only with your consent and you can withdraw it for future use.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">5) Who we share data with</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">We keep sharing tight and minimal. We may share data with:</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>Website hosting / infrastructure providers (to run the website)</li>
              <li>Email/phone/WhatsApp providers (when you contact us that way)</li>
              <li>Professional advisers (accountant) if needed</li>
              <li>Law enforcement/regulators if we’re legally required</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2">We do not sell your personal data.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">6) International transfers</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">Some providers (e.g., website tools, email platforms) may process data outside the UK. If that happens, we rely on appropriate safeguards (like adequacy regulations or standard contractual clauses) as required under UK GDPR.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">7) How long we keep your data (retention)</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">We keep personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes above, then delete or anonymise it. The ICO expects you to state retention periods (or at least the criteria).</p>
            <p class="mt-2">Typical approach (edit to match your reality):</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>Enquiries: up to 12 months after last contact</li>
              <li>Customer/job records: up to 6 years (for accounting/tax and resolving issues)</li>
              <li>Marketing: until you unsubscribe/withdraw consent</li>
              <li>Photos for portfolio: until you withdraw consent (future use stops)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">8) Your rights</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">You have rights over your personal data, including:</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>Access (ask for a copy)</li>
              <li>Rectification (fix inaccurate data)</li>
              <li>Erasure (delete data, where applicable)</li>
              <li>Restriction (pause use)</li>
              <li>Objection (to certain processing, like legitimate interests)</li>
              <li>Data portability (in some cases)</li>
              <li>Withdraw consent (if we rely on consent)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2">To exercise rights, contact us using the details above.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">9) Complaints</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">If you’re unhappy with how we handle data, please contact us first — we’ll try to fix it fast.</p>
            <p>You also have the right to complain to the UK regulator, the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO).</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">10) Security</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">We use reasonable safeguards to protect personal information (access controls, secure devices/accounts, and standard hosting security). No system is invincible — but we don’t leave the door wide open either.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">11) Children</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">Our services and website are not aimed at children. If a child’s information is provided to us, we only use it to respond and provide the requested service, and we minimise what we keep.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">12) Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">If our website uses cookies (or similar tech), we will:</p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
              <li>explain what they do and why,</li>
              <li>and request consent for non-essential cookies (like analytics/marketing).</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2">Essential cookies (strictly necessary for the site to work) may be used without consent.</p>
            <p class="mt-2">Quick setup note (edit this line to match your site):</p>
            <p>We currently use: [NONE / Essential only / Analytics (e.g., Google Analytics) / Other]</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-black">13) Changes to this notice</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">We may update this notice occasionally. The “Last updated” date at the top will change, and the newest version will live on this page.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer30 />
  </body>
</html>
